al risk factors for histoplasmosis include road construction, roofing, bridge and water tower work, demolition, and masonry.\nConclusions\u2014Histoplasmosis can result in considerable morbidity. Increased awareness of disease risk factors among the public and the international healthcare community will improve the timely diagnosis and treatment of histoplasmosis and prevent disease progression and dissemination.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Diaz, James H.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/e66e9e1c06e42e8cb0a50e99d3d5be11", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/0d2e24bc0d95871b33a49a70b464220ad32025ea96aa734cf2c7d7b06b18c2ae", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/TPYUZPP2", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/TPYUZPP2", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/6197da5b40663f99e329f551b074cdd7!/b24678-27115", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/ce1e7618f237ff56e74d51f496e811a3", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"issue": "4", "pages": "531-540", "title": "Wilderness & Environmental Medicine", "volume": "29"}, "alternate_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/e66e9e1c06e42e8cb0a50e99d3d5be11"}, {"identifier": "urn:lsid:zotero.org:groups:5435545:items:TPYUZPP2"}, {"identifier": "10.1016/j.wem.2018.06.008"}]